                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>If a capuchin damages a creature with its jaws Strike, the creature gains both a blessing and a curse that last for [[/r 1d6 #hours]] hours.</p>\n<p>While the blessing doubles the amount of time that the affected creature can hold its breath, the curse imposes a quickened version of the capuchin’s moisture dependency, taking [[/r 1d6]] damage every 10 minutes they go without water.</p>\n<p>A cursed creature can fully immerse itself in water as a 3-action activity to attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"17\" data-pf2-traits=\"curse,divine,transmutation\" data-pf2-label=\"Capuchin’s Curse DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude</span> save, ending both the blessing and the curse on a success.</p>"
                },
